â€¢â€¢Example FormField:

<label for="name">Name</label>
<input name="name" id="name">

â€¢â€¢Autofill works by saving either saving the Name or ID. Then next time you visit a website, and its value is the same name or ID, then it will automatically fill from your storage memory.â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢Use the :autofill CSS pseudo-class to style the form controls that the browser has autofilled.â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢Use :autofill & the prefixed version :-webkit-autofill for the best browser compatibility.â€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢Try to use the autocomplete tag whenever possibleâ€¢â€¢

â€¢â€¢ Examples:
autocomplete="billing postal-code"
autocomplete="email
autocomplete="new-password
autocomplete="current-password
autocomplete="one-time-code"
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
â€¢â€¢â€¢Example of Autocomplete:

<main>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <form>
      <div>
        <label for="address-one">Address line</label>
        <input autocomplete="address-line1" required type="text" id="address-one" name="address-one">
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="city">City</label>
        <input autocomplete="address-level2" required type="text" id="city" name="city">
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="state">State / Province / Region (optional)</label>
        <input autcomplete="address-level1" type="text" id="state" name="state">
      </div>
      <div>
 <label for="zip">ZIP / Postal code (optional)</label>
        <input autocomplete="postal-code" type="text" id="zip" name="zip">
      </div>
      <div>
 <label for="country">Country</label>
        <input autocomplete="country" type="text" id="country" name="country">
      </div>
      <button>Save address</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</main>

â€¢â€¢CSS Value:
 button {
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

label {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
â€¢â€¢Autocomplete Example:

<main>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <form>
      <div>
 <label for="email">Email</label>
        <input autocomplete="email" required type="email" id="email" name="email">
      </div>
      <div>
 <label for="password">Password</label>
        <input autocomplete="new-password" type="password" id="password" name="password">
      </div>
      <button>Sign up</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</main>

â€¢â€¢CSS Value:
 button {
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

label {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}
